label: A2B_tI24_107_2abc_2ab-001
title: Low Temperature UP$_{2}$ Structure
comments:
At temperatures above 83$^\circ$C UP$_{2}$ transforms into its \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_tP6_129_ac_c-002}{high-temperature structure}. (Gerward, 1990) 
 The current structure is very close to the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_tP6_129_ac_c-001}{Cu$_{2}$Sb ($C38)$ structure}.  Indeed, if we allow an uncertainty of 0.3{\AA} FINDSYM puts this in the $C38$ structure. 
 The ICSD entry is from the earlier work of (Pietrasko, 1971).
